title: After Sweeps, 'Dogs Duo Wins NSIC Honors
text:
After Sweeps, 'Dogs Duo Wins NSIC Honors 
By Zach Schneider October 5, 2015 Updated Oct 5, 2015 at 10:47 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) senior setter Ashley Hinsch and junior outside hitter Taylor Wissbroecker have been named Northern Sun Intercollegiate Conference (NSIC) players of the week, it was announced on Monday afternoon. 
Hinsch is the NSIC setter of the week after finishing with 85 assists in wins over Mary and Minot State, which averaged out to 14.17 assists per set. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
Wissbroecker, meanwhile, is the NSIC offensive player of the week after finishing with 31 kills in the two matches and only five attack errors. 
Both players were part of a UMD offense that operated at a .490 hitting percentage through the two weekend matches.
